Description: Part of a jar-seal: of dark brown clay, bearing an impressed inscription. Surface of clay worn, but otherwise in good condition.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXVI, 58; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.69, abb.250A; see also vols. I, 138 and II, 815, n.802;1126.
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Rev George Denis Nash
